                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.887,
                                "byte_start": 76800,
                                "byte_stop": 116402,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in 72-1148, Cupp against Naughten will be announced by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.887,
                        "stop": 151.023,
                        "byte_start": 116402,
                        "byte_stop": 680960,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15141,
                            "name": "William H. Rehnquist",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_h_rehnquist",
                            "last_name": "Rehnquist",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2787,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 528094800,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2787"
                                },
                                {
                                    "id": 2788,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 1125723600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2788"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32786,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 46923,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_rehnquist.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12293,
                            "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.887,
                                "stop": 14.957,
                                "byte_start": 116402,
                                "byte_stop": 136673,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.957,
                                "stop": 24.64,
                                "byte_start": 136673,
                                "byte_stop": 175438,
                                "text": "Respondent Naughten was convicted in an Oregon State Court for the crime of armed robbery, and his conviction was upheld by the Oregon Appellate Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.64,
                                "stop": 29.648,
                                "byte_start": 175438,
                                "byte_stop": 195396,
                                "text": "He then sought federal habeas corpus in the United States District Court in Oregon, was turned on."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.648,
                                "stop": 33.818,
                                "byte_start": 195396,
                                "byte_stop": 212114,
                                "text": "He appealed to the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and prevailed there."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.818,
                                "stop": 49.648,
                                "byte_start": 212114,
                                "byte_stop": 275435,
                                "text": "That court found that a so-called presumption of truthfulness instruction, given at respondent\u2019s trial, had the affect of shifting the burden of proof from the state to him and denied him a fair trial in violation of the Fourteenth Amendment of the United States Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.648,
                                "stop": 70.167,
                                "byte_start": 275435,
                                "byte_stop": 357564,
                                "text": "The instruction in question read as follows: \u201cEvery witness is presumed to speak the truth. This presumption may be overcome by the manner in which the witness testifies, by the nature of his or her testimony, by evidence affecting his or her character, interest, or motives, by contradictory evidence, or by a presumption.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.167,
                                "stop": 83.667,
                                "byte_start": 357564,
                                "byte_stop": 411481,
                                "text": "Along with this instruction, the Trial Court gave lengthy instructions, telling the jury that the burden was on the State to prove respondent\u2019s guilt beyond a reasonable doubt, and the respondent was entitled to the benefit of the presumption of innocence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.667,
                                "stop": 94.764,
                                "byte_start": 411481,
                                "byte_stop": 455889,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals placed a good deal of reliance on the fact that a large number of federal courts of appeals have disapproved this instruction when given by a federal district court in a federal trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.764,
                                "stop": 99.256,
                                "byte_start": 455889,
                                "byte_stop": 473861,
                                "text": "We do not attach the same weight to this fact or as did the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.256,
                                "stop": 105.416,
                                "byte_start": 473861,
                                "byte_stop": 498521,
                                "text": "These courts of appeals have supervisory authority over the federal district courts within their jurisdictions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.416,
                                "stop": 115.273,
                                "byte_start": 498521,
                                "byte_stop": 537913,
                                "text": "They have a good deal of latitude to condemn jury instructions given by those courts and to reverse convictions resulting from trials in which those instructions have been given."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.273,
                                "stop": 122.953,
                                "byte_start": 537913,
                                "byte_stop": 568633,
                                "text": "But a federal habeas court, reviewing a state conviction, may grant relief only if the asserted errors of constitutional dimension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.953,
                                "stop": 139.371,
                                "byte_start": 568633,
                                "byte_stop": 634358,
                                "text": "We conclude that whatever maybe the shortcomings of this instruction the abstract, when read in the context of the other instructions given by the trial court, it neither shifted the burden of proof to the respondent, no water down the State\u2019s burden of proving guilt beyond a reasonable doubt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.371,
                                "stop": 151.023,
                                "byte_start": 634358,
                                "byte_stop": 680960,
                                "text": "We, therefore, reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals. Mr. Justice Brennan has filed a dissenting opinion in which Mr. Justice Douglas and Mr. Justice Marshall joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
